My Story:

I was born to a nurse, whose father is a nuclear scientist. My father works for the Department of Defence, whose parents are from the Netherlands, and Queensland.

I was born in Adelaide, but migrated to Canberra just before my sister was born in Canberra. My day-care was next to the hospital, so my mum could pick me up when her shift was done.

I went to primary school in Weston Creek, from 2011 to 2017, and moved to Marist in 2018. I was initially placed in MC9, but was moved to MC1 because all the -9 house groups were shut down in 2017. I am now in Year 11, and hope to do great things in the future.

# Introduction

**Here are the things you need to learn in this module:**

  
1) Stories convey meaning, usually rich meaning  
2) Stories address human needs, the better they do this, the longer they last  
3) Stories address issues that give meaning to life, for example:  
• The purpose of humans  
• Why things are the way they are  
• Values  
• A cultural Identity  
• The nature of god/s  
• The relationship between people and their environment  
• The relationship between people and god

Consider this exploration of myths (a type of story) and how myths do the above.
